Priority: optional
Description: openmediavault Open Adaptive RAID (OAR) plugin
 This plugin is used to create, manage, and monitor Open Adaptive RAID storage
 pools. A pool combines disks of mixed sizes into a single expandable
 volume that tolerates the failure of one disk. Each disk is sliced into
 size tiers, every tier is protected by an mdadm RAID5 array with PPL
 write-hole protection, and the arrays are aggregated into an LVM volume
 group carrying a single logical volume formatted with BTRFS, EXT4, XFS or JFS.
 Pools can be grown online by adding disks of arbitrary sizes.
